				<p class="post-meta">  <span class="published">Nov 22, 2019</span>    </p><div class="post-content"><div id="attachment_5243" style="width: 778px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><a href="https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2019/11/RJD_04_01_0022_0001_005.jpg"><img class="size-full wp-image-5243" src="https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2019/11/RJD_04_01_0022_0001_005.jpg" alt="Mayor Richard J. Daley speaks at a Chicago City Council memorial for President John F. Kennedy, 1963" width="768" height="949" srcset="https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2019/11/RJD_04_01_0022_0001_005.jpg 768w, https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2019/11/RJD_04_01_0022_0001_005-243x300.jpg 243w" sizes="(max-width: 768px) 100vw, 768px" /></a><p class="wp-caption-text">Mayor Richard J. Daley speaks at a Chicago City Council memorial for President John F. Kennedy, 1963. Photo credit: Sorich. RJD_04_01_0022_0001_005</p></div>
