			<article id="post-5178" class="et_pb_post clearfix et_pb_no_thumb post-5178 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-news-and-research-funds">

			
												<h2 class="entry-title"><a href="https://rjd.library.uic.edu/the-road-to-con-con/">The road to Con-Con</a></h2>
				
				<p class="post-meta">  <span class="published">Nov 18, 2019</span>    </p><div class="post-content"><p>Fifty years ago today, on November 18, 1969, Richard M. Daley won his first election&#8211;as delegate to the Illinois Constitutional Convention, or &#8220;Con-Con&#8221; for short. The convention drafted a new constitution for the state, and voters ratified it soon afterward. Daley went on to serve as senator in the state legislature (1973-1981), state&#8217;s attorney for Cook County (1981-1989), and mayor of Chicago (1989-2011).</p>
<div id="attachment_5209" style="width: 122px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><a href="https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2019/10/RJD_02_01_0093_0001_001.jpg"><img class="size-medium wp-image-5209" src="https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2019/10/RJD_02_01_0093_0001_001-112x300.jpg" alt="First page of a voter's guide to the new Illinois Constitution, 1970" width="112" height="300" srcset="https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2019/10/RJD_02_01_0093_0001_001-112x300.jpg 112w, https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2019/10/RJD_02_01_0093_0001_001-382x1024.jpg 382w, https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2019/10/RJD_02_01_0093_0001_001.jpg 603w" sizes="(max-width: 112px) 100vw, 112px" /></a><p class="wp-caption-text">First page of a voter&#8217;s guide to the new Illinois Constitution, 1970. RJD_02_01_0093_0001_001</p></div>
</div>			
			</article> <!-- .et_pb_post -->
	
			<article id="post-5130" class="et_pb_post clearfix et_pb_no_thumb post-5130 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-news-and-research-funds">

			
												<h2 class="entry-title"><a href="https://rjd.library.uic.edu/remembering-1989-mayor-richard-m-daley-welcomes-lech-walesa/">Remembering 1989: Mayor Richard M. Daley welcomes Lech Walesa</a></h2>
				
				<p class="post-meta">  <span class="published">Nov 7, 2019</span>    </p><div class="post-content"><p>Lech Walesa led Solidarity, aÂ workers&#8217; movement that resisted Poland&#8217;s Communist government. Solidarity&#8217;s success in securing freer elections contributed to ending the Cold War.</p>
<p>Thirty years ago this month, in November 1989, Walesa visited the United States. He stopped in Chicago, which has one of the world&#8217;s largest populations of Polish speakers. Mayor Richard M. Daley, Governor James R. Thompson, and other officials welcomed Walesa and held a luncheon in his honor.</p>
<div id="attachment_5166" style="width: 310px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><a href="https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2019/10/RMD_07_0062_0010_002_030A.jpg"><img class="size-medium wp-image-5166" src="https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2019/10/RMD_07_0062_0010_002_030A-300x200.jpg" alt="Lech Walesa addresses a Chicago gathering as Mayor Richard M. Daley applauds, November 18, 1989" width="300" height="200" srcset="https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2019/10/RMD_07_0062_0010_002_030A-300x200.jpg 300w, https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2019/10/RMD_07_0062_0010_002_030A-768x512.jpg 768w, https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2019/10/RMD_07_0062_0010_002_030A-1024x683.jpg 1024w, https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2019/10/RMD_07_0062_0010_002_030A-1080x720.jpg 1080w, https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2019/10/RMD_07_0062_0010_002_030A.jpg 1200w" sizes="(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px" /></a><p class="wp-caption-text">Lech Walesa addresses a Chicago gathering as Mayor Richard M. Daley applauds, November 18, 1989. RMD_07_0062_0010_002_030A</p></div>
<div id="attachment_5167" style="width: 310px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><a href="https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2019/10/RMD_07_0062_0010_003_017A.jpg"><img class="size-medium wp-image-5167" src="https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2019/10/RMD_07_0062_0010_003_017A-300x200.jpg" alt="Mayor Richard M. Daley speaks with Lech Walesa at a dinner to honor the Polish leader. Illinois Governor James R. Thompson looks on, November 18, 1989" width="300" height="200" srcset="https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2019/10/RMD_07_0062_0010_003_017A-300x200.jpg 300w, https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2019/10/RMD_07_0062_0010_003_017A-768x512.jpg 768w, https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2019/10/RMD_07_0062_0010_003_017A-1024x683.jpg 1024w, https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2019/10/RMD_07_0062_0010_003_017A-1080x720.jpg 1080w, https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2019/10/RMD_07_0062_0010_003_017A.jpg 1200w" sizes="(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px" /></a><p class="wp-caption-text">Mayor Richard M. Daley speaks with Lech Walesa at a dinner to honor the Polish leader. Illinois Governor James R. Thompson looks on, November 18, 1989. RMD_07_0062_0010_003_017A</p></div>
<p>A little more than a year after this visit, Walesa was elected president of Poland.</p>
</div>			
			</article> <!-- .et_pb_post -->
	
			<article id="post-5220" class="et_pb_post clearfix et_pb_no_thumb post-5220 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-news-and-research-funds">

			
												<h2 class="entry-title"><a href="https://rjd.library.uic.edu/bill-daleys-uics-wiewel-lecture-on-economic-development/">Bill Daley&#8217;s UIC&#8217;s Wiewel Lecture on Economic Development</a></h2>
				
				<p class="post-meta">  <span class="published">Oct 31, 2019</span>    </p><div class="post-content"><p>(Reposted from UICToday. &#8220;<a href="https://today.uic.edu/daley-its-good-business-for-business-to-be-a-good-social-partner">Daley: It&#8217;s &#8216;good business&#8217; for business to be a good social partner</a>&#8220;: October 28, 2019, updated October 29, 2019. For UIC&#8217;s announcement about the lecture, see &#8220;<a href="https://today.uic.edu/william-bill-daley-to-discuss-roles-of-corporations-in-society-as-he-donates-papers-to-uic">William âBillâ Daley to discuss roles of corporations in society as he donates papers to UIC</a>&#8221; To research the collection, please visit the <a href="https://findingaids.library.uic.edu/sc/MSWMD_01.xml">finding aid (inventory list) for the William D. Daley papers</a>)</p>
<div id="attachment_84839" style="width: 275px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img class="wp-image-84839" style="font-weight: bold" src="https://today.uic.edu/files/2019/10/102319_Bill-Daley-Lecture_JC0093b-265x406.jpg" alt="William âBillâ Daley presents the Wiewel Lecture on economic development in UICâs Academic and Residential Complex" width="265" height="406" /><p class="wp-caption-text">William âBillâ Daley presents the Wiewel Lecture on economic development in UICâs Academic and Residential Complex. Photo: Joshua Clark</p></div>
<div class="pf-content">
<div class="wp-block-image"></div>
<p>Between the time that William âBillâ Daley served as President Bill Clintonâs secretary of commerce and when he served as President Barack Obamaâs chief of staff, the internet had taken over the world and completely changed the way business and politics were conducted.</p>
<p>Daley, who gave the Wiewel Lecture on Economic Development at the University of Illinois at Chicago on Oct. 23, tapped into his extensive background at the crossroads of business and politics to speak to about 100 people, including students, faculty, elected officials and family members.</p>
<p>In his lecture, âCorporations &amp; Humanity: Why They Belong Together,â Daley focused on how the role of corporations had shifted because of technology and the rise in social media that made companies â as well as political leaders â more accountable more quickly.</p>
<p> <a href="https://rjd.library.uic.edu/bill-daleys-uics-wiewel-lecture-on-economic-development/#more-5220" class="more-link">read more&#8230;</a></div>
</div>			
			</article> <!-- .et_pb_post -->
	
			<article id="post-5124" class="et_pb_post clearfix et_pb_no_thumb post-5124 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-news-and-research-funds">

			
												<h2 class="entry-title"><a href="https://rjd.library.uic.edu/remembering-1989-mayor-richard-m-daley-announces-greenstreets-program/">Remembering 1989: Mayor Richard M. Daley announces &#8220;GreenStreets&#8221; program</a></h2>
				
				<p class="post-meta">  <span class="published">Oct 26, 2019</span>    </p><div class="post-content"><p>Thirty years ago today, on October 26, 1989, Mayor Richard M. Daley announced Chicago&#8217;s new &#8220;GreenStreets&#8221; program. The goal of the program was to add a half million trees to what &#8220;Chicago&#8217;s urban forest.&#8221; On the day of the announcement, Daley chipped in, helping plant a tree on the 8100 south block of Marquette.</p>
<div id="attachment_5153" style="width: 210px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><a href="https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2019/09/RMD_07_0061_0019_005_033.jpg"><img class="size-medium wp-image-5153" src="https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2019/09/RMD_07_0061_0019_005_033-200x300.jpg" alt="Mayor Richard M. Daley plants a tree for Chicago's GreenStreets program, October 26, 1989" width="200" height="300" srcset="https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2019/09/RMD_07_0061_0019_005_033-200x300.jpg 200w, https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2019/09/RMD_07_0061_0019_005_033-768x1153.jpg 768w, https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2019/09/RMD_07_0061_0019_005_033-682x1024.jpg 682w, https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2019/09/RMD_07_0061_0019_005_033.jpg 799w" sizes="(max-width: 200px) 100vw, 200px" /></a><p class="wp-caption-text">Mayor Richard M. Daley plants a tree for Chicago&#8217;s GreenStreets program, October 26, 1989. RMD_07_0061_0019_005_033</p></div>
<h2>Source consulted</h2>
<p>&#8220;Mayor Daley kicks off &#8216;GreenStreets,&#8217; Chicago&#8217;s tree planting program,&#8221; October 26, 1989. Richard M. Daley papers, Special Collections and University Archives, University of Illinois at Chicago. Box 3-3, folder 24.</p>
</div>			
