												<h2 class="entry-title"><a href="https://rjd.library.uic.edu/a-chicago-landmark-the-aon-center-formerly-standard-oil-building/">A Chicago landmark: the Aon Center, formerly Standard Oil Building</a></h2>
				
				<p class="post-meta">  <span class="published">Sep 27, 2019</span>    </p><div class="post-content"><p>The Aon Center, originally called the Standard Oil building, is one of the tallest skyscrapers in Chicago.</p>
<h2>ChicagoÂ  Mayor Richard J. Daley inspects the plans</h2>
<div id="attachment_5148" style="width: 310px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><a href="https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2019/09/RJD_04_01_0026_0020_001.jpg"><img class="size-medium wp-image-5148" src="https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2019/09/RJD_04_01_0026_0020_001-300x243.jpg" alt="Mayor Richard J. Daley and John Swearingen, President of Standard Oil, view an architectural model of the Standard Oil Building (now Aon Center), circa 1967" width="300" height="243" srcset="https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2019/09/RJD_04_01_0026_0020_001-300x243.jpg 300w, https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2019/09/RJD_04_01_0026_0020_001-768x623.jpg 768w, https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2019/09/RJD_04_01_0026_0020_001.jpg 998w" sizes="(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px" /></a><p class="wp-caption-text">Mayor Richard J. Daley and John Swearingen, President of Standard Oil, view an architectural model of the Standard Oil Building (now Aon Center), circa 1967. RJD_04_01_0026_0020_001</p></div>
<h2>Groundbreaking!</h2>
<div id="attachment_5149" style="width: 310px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><a href="https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2019/09/RJD_04_01_0026_0020_002.jpg"><img class="size-medium wp-image-5149" src="https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2019/09/RJD_04_01_0026_0020_002-300x245.jpg" alt="Mayor Richard J. Daley and John Swearingen, President of Standard Oil, stand next to an architectural model of the Standard Oil Building (now Aon Center) at the groundbreaking ceremony for that building. Two unidentified men are behind them at the right, 1967" width="300" height="245" srcset="https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2019/09/RJD_04_01_0026_0020_002-300x245.jpg 300w, https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2019/09/RJD_04_01_0026_0020_002-768x627.jpg 768w, https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2019/09/RJD_04_01_0026_0020_002.jpg 951w" sizes="(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px" /></a><p class="wp-caption-text">Mayor Richard J. Daley and John Swearingen, President of Standard Oil, stand next to an architectural model of the Standard Oil Building (now Aon Center) at the groundbreaking ceremony for that building. Two unidentified men are behind them at the right, 1967. RJD_04_01_0026_0020_002</p></div>
