			<article id="post-5017" class="et_pb_post clearfix et_pb_no_thumb post-5017 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-news-and-research-funds">

			
												<h2 class="entry-title"><a href="https://rjd.library.uic.edu/celebrating-the-moon-landing/">Celebrating the moon landing</a></h2>
				
				<p class="post-meta">  <span class="published">Jul 20, 2019</span>    </p><div class="post-content"><p style="text-align: left">Today marks the 50th anniversary of the first landing on the moon by the Apollo 11 astronauts. After the astronauts&#8217; return to earth, Chicago honored them with a parade downtown.</p>
<div id="attachment_5031" style="width: 310px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><a href="https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2019/07/RJD_04_01_0052_0006_011.jpg"><img class="size-medium wp-image-5031" src="https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2019/07/RJD_04_01_0052_0006_011-300x212.jpg" alt="A large banner saying &quot;That's One Small Step for a Man One Giant Leap for Mankind&quot; hangs over a City Hall entranceway on LaSalle Street. A group of people are sitting on the curb waiting along the parade route, August 13, 1969" width="300" height="212" srcset="https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2019/07/RJD_04_01_0052_0006_011-300x212.jpg 300w, https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2019/07/RJD_04_01_0052_0006_011-768x542.jpg 768w, https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2019/07/RJD_04_01_0052_0006_011-400x284.jpg 400w, https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2019/07/RJD_04_01_0052_0006_011.jpg 954w" sizes="(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px" /></a><p class="wp-caption-text">A large banner saying &#8220;That&#8217;s One Small Step for a Man One Giant Leap for Mankind&#8221; hangs over a City Hall entranceway on LaSalle Street. A group of people are sitting on the curb waiting along the parade route, August 13, 1969. RJD_04_01_0052_0006_011</p></div>
<p style="text-align: left">As many as two million spectators may have witnessed it, according to Police Superintendent James B. Conlisk.</p>
<p style="text-align: left">Michael Kilian and John MacLean, of theÂ <em>Chicago Tribune</em>, described the parade:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style="text-align: left">It was more than a parade, it was glory. The brilliant blue sky was filled with ticker tape that seemed without source, streets and avenues were no longer thorofares [<em>sic</em>] but masses of humanity, and the cheers, the sirens, the ringing bells created so great a din that no other sound could be heard.</p>
</blockquote>
<div id="attachment_1095" style="width: 310px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><a href="https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2015/05/RJD_04_01_0052_0006_013.jpg"><img class="size-medium wp-image-1095" src="https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2015/05/RJD_04_01_0052_0006_013-300x200.jpg" alt="Apollo 11 astronaut parade crowd to celebrate landing of first man on the moon, August 13, 1969" width="300" height="200" srcset="https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2015/05/RJD_04_01_0052_0006_013-300x200.jpg 300w, https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2015/05/RJD_04_01_0052_0006_013-1024x684.jpg 1024w, https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2015/05/RJD_04_01_0052_0006_013-1080x721.jpg 1080w, https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2015/05/RJD_04_01_0052_0006_013.jpg 1500w" sizes="(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px" /></a><p class="wp-caption-text">Apollo 11 astronaut parade crowd to celebrate landing of first man on the moon, August 13, 1969. RJD_04_01_0052_0006_013</p></div>
<div id="attachment_5033" style="width: 310px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><a href="https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2019/07/RJD_04_01_0052_0006_017.jpg"><img class="size-medium wp-image-5033" src="https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2019/07/RJD_04_01_0052_0006_017-300x213.jpg" alt="Mayor Richard J. Daley speaks from the podium at a ceremony in Civic Center plaza to honor Apollo 11 astronauts Neil Armstrong, Edwin &quot;Buzz&quot; Aldrin, and Michael Collins, August 13, 1969" width="300" height="213" srcset="https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2019/07/RJD_04_01_0052_0006_017-300x213.jpg 300w, https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2019/07/RJD_04_01_0052_0006_017-768x545.jpg 768w, https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2019/07/RJD_04_01_0052_0006_017-400x284.jpg 400w, https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2019/07/RJD_04_01_0052_0006_017.jpg 949w" sizes="(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px" /></a><p class="wp-caption-text">Mayor Richard J. Daley speaks from the podium at a ceremony in Civic Center plaza to honor Apollo 11 astronauts Neil Armstrong, Edwin &#8220;Buzz&#8221; Aldrin, and Michael Collins, August 13, 1969. RJD_04_01_0052_0006_017</p></div>
<h2>Source consulted</h2>
<p>Michael Kilian and John Maclean, &#8220;Wild Acclaim for Heroes,&#8221;Â <em>Chicago Tribune</em>, August 14, 1969, p. N1.</p>
