			<article id="post-4910" class="et_pb_post clearfix et_pb_no_thumb post-4910 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-news-and-research-funds">

			
												<h2 class="entry-title"><a href="https://rjd.library.uic.edu/remembering-1989-mayor-richard-m-daleys-first-taste-of-chicago-appearance/">Remembering 1989: Mayor Richard M. Daley&#8217;s first Taste of Chicago appearance</a></h2>
				
				<p class="post-meta">  <span class="published">Jun 27, 2019</span>    </p><div class="post-content"><p>Today marks the 30th anniversary of Mayor Richard M. Daley&#8217;s first appearance at the city&#8217;s annual Taste of Chicago event.</p>
<div id="attachment_4950" style="width: 310px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><a href="https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2019/06/RMD_07_0059_0001_Negative_TasteOfChicago1-3JP_12A.jpg"><img class="size-medium wp-image-4950" src="https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2019/06/RMD_07_0059_0001_Negative_TasteOfChicago1-3JP_12A-300x201.jpg" alt="Mayor Richard M. Daley enjoys corn on the cob at the Taste of Chicago event, June 27, 1989" width="300" height="201" srcset="https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2019/06/RMD_07_0059_0001_Negative_TasteOfChicago1-3JP_12A-300x201.jpg 300w, https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2019/06/RMD_07_0059_0001_Negative_TasteOfChicago1-3JP_12A-768x515.jpg 768w, https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2019/06/RMD_07_0059_0001_Negative_TasteOfChicago1-3JP_12A-1024x687.jpg 1024w, https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2019/06/RMD_07_0059_0001_Negative_TasteOfChicago1-3JP_12A-1080x725.jpg 1080w" sizes="(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px" /></a><p class="wp-caption-text">Mayor Richard M. Daley enjoys corn on the cob at the Taste of Chicago event, June 27, 1989. RMD_07_0059_0001_004_012A</p></div>
<p>The event had begun in 1980 under Mayor Jane Byrne and at that time had featured more than forty Chicago-area restaurants and lasted one day. By 1989, when Daley became mayor, seventy-seven restaurants were represented, and the event itself ran from June 27 through July 4.</p>
<div id="attachment_4954" style="width: 310px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><a href="https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2019/06/RMD_07_0059_0001_Negative_TasteOfChicago2-3JP_18A.jpg"><img class="size-medium wp-image-4954" src="https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2019/06/RMD_07_0059_0001_Negative_TasteOfChicago2-3JP_18A-300x201.jpg" alt="Chicago Mayor Richard M. Daley greets visitors to the Taste of Chicago event, June 27, 1989" width="300" height="201" srcset="https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2019/06/RMD_07_0059_0001_Negative_TasteOfChicago2-3JP_18A-300x201.jpg 300w, https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2019/06/RMD_07_0059_0001_Negative_TasteOfChicago2-3JP_18A-768x514.jpg 768w, https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2019/06/RMD_07_0059_0001_Negative_TasteOfChicago2-3JP_18A-1024x685.jpg 1024w, https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2019/06/RMD_07_0059_0001_Negative_TasteOfChicago2-3JP_18A-1080x723.jpg 1080w" sizes="(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px" /></a><p class="wp-caption-text">Chicago Mayor Richard M. Daley greets visitors to the Taste of Chicago event, June 27, 1989. RMD_07_0059_0001_005_018A</p></div>
<p>On the day of the event, Mayor Daley said:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style="text-align: left">I can&#8217;t think of any other place I&#8217;d rather be than here at our great Taste of Chicago food fair. There&#8217;s music, fu, an dmore than 70 restaurants are here to take your order! We expect more than a milion people to come out Monday for our special Fourth of July fireworks display and concert featuring the Grant Park Symphony.</p>
</blockquote>
<h2>Sources consulted</h2>
<p>Lewis, Antoine. &#8220;Taste also whets the other senses.&#8221;Â <em>Chicago Tribune</em>. June 28, 1989, p. 3.</p>
<p>&#8220;Remarks: Mayor Daley Opens Taste of Chicago,&#8221; Richard M. Daley papers, University of Illinois at Chicago, series 3, box 3-2, folder 10.</p>
<p>Tackett, Michael. &#8220;Du Jour.&#8221;Â <em>Chicago Tribune</em>. June 30, 1989, p. C1.</p>
<p>Vettel, Phil. &#8220;Taste if full of don&#8217;t-miss eating delights.&#8221;Â <em>Chicago Tribune.</em>Â June 28, 1989, p. 20.</p>
</div>			
			</article> <!-- .et_pb_post -->
	
			<article id="post-4859" class="et_pb_post clearfix et_pb_no_thumb post-4859 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-news-and-research-funds">

			
												<h2 class="entry-title"><a href="https://rjd.library.uic.edu/remembering-1989-chicago-mayor-richard-m-daley-leads-the-gay-pride-parade/">Remembering 1989: Chicago Mayor Richard M. Daley leads the Gay Pride Parade</a></h2>
				
				<p class="post-meta">  <span class="published">Jun 25, 2019</span>    </p><div class="post-content"><p>Thirty years ago today, on June 25, 1989, and only two months after being sworn in as mayor of Chicago, Richard M. Daley led the city&#8217;s gay pride parade. He was not the first Chicago mayor to participate, as Harold Washington (1983-1987) had attended while he was mayor. However, the local newspapers credited Mayor Daley as being the first to actually lead the parade.</p>
<div id="attachment_4869" style="width: 1034px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><a href="https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2019/05/RMD_07_0058_0026_Negative_GayParade3_013.jpg"><img class="size-large wp-image-4869" src="https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2019/05/RMD_07_0058_0026_Negative_GayParade3_013-1024x686.jpg" alt="Chicago Mayor Richard M. Daley, seated in car, greets a well wisher at the city's gay pride parade, June 25, 1989" width="1024" height="686" srcset="https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2019/05/RMD_07_0058_0026_Negative_GayParade3_013-1024x686.jpg 1024w, https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2019/05/RMD_07_0058_0026_Negative_GayParade3_013-300x201.jpg 300w, https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2019/05/RMD_07_0058_0026_Negative_GayParade3_013-768x515.jpg 768w, https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2019/05/RMD_07_0058_0026_Negative_GayParade3_013-1080x724.jpg 1080w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /></a><p class="wp-caption-text">Chicago Mayor Richard M. Daley, seated in car, greets a well wisher at the city&#8217;s gay pride parade, June 25, 1989. RMD_07_0058_0026_003_013</p></div>
<h2>Sources consulted</h2>
<p>Griffin, Jean Latz. &#8220;Mayoral Hopefuls Support Gay Voters.&#8221;Â <em>Chicago Tribune</em>. February 5, 1987, page 1.</p>
<p>Page, Clarence. &#8220;Dealing with Gay Parades.&#8221;Â <em>Chicago Tribune</em>. July 7, 1985, page 3.</p>
<p>Rotenberk, Lori. &#8220;Daley is first mayor to lead gays&#8217; parade.&#8221;Â <em>Chicago Sun-Times</em>. June 26, 1989, page 3. <em>Newsbank</em>. &lt;<a href="https://infoweb.newsbank.com/apps/news/openurl?ctx_ver=z39.882004&amp;rft_id=info%3Asid/infoweb.newsbank.com&amp;svc_dat=AWNB&amp;req_dat=0FD3D1C913B1A06F&amp;rft_val_format=info%3Aofi/fmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Actx&amp;rft_dat=document_id%3Anews%252F0EB36E660D6EB884">https://infoweb.newsbank.com/apps/news/openurl?ctx_ver=z39.882004&amp;rft_id=info%3Asid/infoweb.newsbank.com&amp;svc_dat=AWNB&amp;req_dat=0FD3D1C913B1A06F&amp;rft_val_format=info%3Aofi/fmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Actx&amp;rft_dat=document_id%3Anews%252F0EB36E660D6EB884</a>&gt; Paywall may apply. Accessed May 17, 2019.</p>
<p>Seigel, Jessica. &#8220;Daley&#8217;s support is inspiration to gay pride parade.&#8221;Â <em>Chicago Tribune</em>. June 26, 1989, page D1 and D3.</p>
