			<article id="post-4850" class="et_pb_post clearfix et_pb_no_thumb post-4850 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-news-and-research-funds">

			
												<h2 class="entry-title"><a href="https://rjd.library.uic.edu/centennial-of-richard-j-daleys-high-school-graduation/">Centennial of Richard J. Daley&#8217;s high school graduation</a></h2>
				
				<p class="post-meta">  <span class="published">Jun 16, 2019</span>    </p><div class="post-content"><p>Today, June 16, 2019, marks the 100th anniversary of Richard J. Daley&#8217;s graduation from his high school, De La Salle Institute. Daley later went on to become Chicago&#8217;s second longest-serving mayor, from 1955 to 1976. His record was surpassed only by his son, Richard M. Daley, who served from 1989 to 2011.</p>
<div id="attachment_4854" style="width: 962px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><a href="https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2019/05/RJD_04_01_0043_0009_002.jpg"><img class="size-full wp-image-4854" src="https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2019/05/RJD_04_01_0043_0009_002.jpg" alt="Richard J. Daley with his senior class at De La Salle Institute (3rd row, 4th from right)" width="952" height="757" srcset="https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2019/05/RJD_04_01_0043_0009_002.jpg 952w, https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2019/05/RJD_04_01_0043_0009_002-300x239.jpg 300w, https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2019/05/RJD_04_01_0043_0009_002-768x611.jpg 768w" sizes="(max-width: 952px) 100vw, 952px" /></a><p class="wp-caption-text">Richard J. Daley with his senior class at De La Salle Institute (3rd row, 4th from right). RJD_04_01_0043_0009_002</p></div>
</div>			
			</article> <!-- .et_pb_post -->
	
