<h2><a style="font-weight: bold;font-size: 14px" href="https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2019/04/RJD_04_01_0023_0005_016.jpg"><img class="size-medium wp-image-4824" src="https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2019/04/RJD_04_01_0023_0005_016-300x217.jpg" alt="Eleanor &quot;Sis&quot; Daley and Mayor Richard J. Daley visit the grotto of Our Lady of Lourdes in Lourdes, France, 1964" width="300" height="217" srcset="https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2019/04/RJD_04_01_0023_0005_016-300x217.jpg 300w, https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2019/04/RJD_04_01_0023_0005_016-768x555.jpg 768w, https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2019/04/RJD_04_01_0023_0005_016.jpg 992w" sizes="(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px" /></a></h2>
<p>Eleanor &#8220;Sis&#8221; Daley and Mayor Richard J. Daley visit the grotto of Our Lady of Lourdes in Lourdes, France, 1964. RJD_04_01_0023_0005_016</p>
<div id="attachment_4756" style="width: 310px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><a href="https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2019/03/RJD_04_01_0023_0005_020.jpg"><img class="size-medium wp-image-4756" src="https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2019/03/RJD_04_01_0023_0005_020-300x244.jpg" alt="Eleanor Daley and Mayor Richard J. Daley meet the Lord Mayor of London, Alderman Clement Harman at Mansion House, 1964" width="300" height="244" srcset="https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2019/03/RJD_04_01_0023_0005_020-300x244.jpg 300w, https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2019/03/RJD_04_01_0023_0005_020-768x624.jpg 768w, https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2019/03/RJD_04_01_0023_0005_020.jpg 950w" sizes="(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px" /></a><p class="wp-caption-text">Eleanor Daley and Mayor Richard J. Daley meet the Lord Mayor of London, Alderman Clement Harman at Mansion House, 1964. RJD_04_01_0023_0005_020</p></div>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<h2>Last stop: &#8220;Ireland, of course&#8221;</h2>
<p>Chicago&#8217;s director of special events, Colonel &#8220;Jack&#8221; Reilly, accompanied Mayor and Mrs. Daley on the trip to Europe. When a reporter for theÂ <em>Chicago Tribune</em>Â asked where the the Mayor&#8217;s last stop would be, Reilly answered,Â &#8220;Heaven.&#8221; He clarified: &#8220;Ireland, of course.&#8221;</p>
<div id="attachment_4846" style="width: 160px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><a href="https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2019/04/RJD_04_01_0023_0012_003.jpg"><img class="size-thumbnail wp-image-4846" src="https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2019/04/RJD_04_01_0023_0012_003-150x150.jpg" alt="Colonel Jack Reilly (left foreground) and others at a candlelight event during a trip to Ireland, 1964" width="150" height="150" /></a><p class="wp-caption-text">Colonel Jack Reilly (left foreground) and others at a candlelight event during a trip to Ireland, 1964. RJD_04_01_0023_0012_003</p></div>
<h3>Irish dignitaries</h3>
<div id="attachment_4787" style="width: 239px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><a href="https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2019/04/RJD_04_01_0023_0012_008.jpg"><img class="size-medium wp-image-4787" src="https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2019/04/RJD_04_01_0023_0012_008-229x300.jpg" alt="Chicago Mayor Richard J. Daley and Eleanor &quot;Sis&quot; Daley with Mayor of Dungarvan, Ireland, Andy Minihan, 1964" width="229" height="300" srcset="https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2019/04/RJD_04_01_0023_0012_008-229x300.jpg 229w, https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2019/04/RJD_04_01_0023_0012_008.jpg 763w" sizes="(max-width: 229px) 100vw, 229px" /></a><p class="wp-caption-text">Chicago Mayor Richard J. Daley and Eleanor &#8220;Sis&#8221; Daley with Mayor of Dungarvan, Ireland, Andy Minihan, 1964. Colm O&#8217;Byrne, photographer. RJD_04_01_0023_0012_008</p></div>
<div id="attachment_4789" style="width: 310px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><a href="https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2019/04/RJD_04_01_0023_0011_004.jpg"><img class="size-medium wp-image-4789" src="https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2019/04/RJD_04_01_0023_0011_004-300x223.jpg" alt="Chicago Mayor Richard J. Daley and Eleanor &quot;Sis&quot; Daley outside with Irish President Eamon de Valera at his home, 1964" width="300" height="223" srcset="https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2019/04/RJD_04_01_0023_0011_004-300x223.jpg 300w, https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2019/04/RJD_04_01_0023_0011_004-768x571.jpg 768w, https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2019/04/RJD_04_01_0023_0011_004.jpg 983w" sizes="(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px" /></a><p class="wp-caption-text">Chicago Mayor Richard J. Daley and Eleanor &#8220;Sis&#8221; Daley outside with Irish President Eamon de Valera at his home, 1964. RJD_04_01_0023_0011_004</p></div>
<h3>Relatives of late United States President John F. Kennedy</h3>
<div id="attachment_4799" style="width: 310px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><a href="https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2019/04/Trip_to_Ireland_Richard_J_and_Eleanor_Daley_with_relatives_of_John_F_Kennedy_and_others.jpg"><img class="size-medium wp-image-4799" src="https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2019/04/Trip_to_Ireland_Richard_J_and_Eleanor_Daley_with_relatives_of_John_F_Kennedy_and_others-300x229.jpg" alt="Trip to Ireland, Richard J. and Eleanor Daley with relatives of John F. Kennedy and others, 1964" width="300" height="229" srcset="https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2019/04/Trip_to_Ireland_Richard_J_and_Eleanor_Daley_with_relatives_of_John_F_Kennedy_and_others-300x229.jpg 300w, https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2019/04/Trip_to_Ireland_Richard_J_and_Eleanor_Daley_with_relatives_of_John_F_Kennedy_and_others-768x585.jpg 768w, https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2019/04/Trip_to_Ireland_Richard_J_and_Eleanor_Daley_with_relatives_of_John_F_Kennedy_and_others.jpg 993w" sizes="(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px" /></a><p class="wp-caption-text">Trip to Ireland, Richard J. and Eleanor Daley with relatives of John F. Kennedy and others, 1964. Colm O&#8217;Byrne, photographer. RJD_04_01_0023_0012_014</p></div>
<h3>County Waterford</h3>
<p>Mayor Daley&#8217;s paternal and maternal ancestors had hailed from County Waterford. In the section of Waterford called Old Parish, Mayor and Mrs. Daley received a warm welcome.</p>
<div id="attachment_4809" style="width: 310px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><a href="https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2019/04/RJD_04_01_0042_0001_034.jpg"><img class="size-medium wp-image-4809" src="https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2019/04/RJD_04_01_0042_0001_034-300x200.jpg" alt="Mayor Richard J. Daley speaks at an Old Parish event to commemorate him during his visit to Ireland. Eleanor &quot;Sis&quot; Daley is among those seated on the dais, 1964" width="300" height="200" srcset="https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2019/04/RJD_04_01_0042_0001_034-300x200.jpg 300w, https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2019/04/RJD_04_01_0042_0001_034-768x511.jpg 768w, https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2019/04/RJD_04_01_0042_0001_034.jpg 940w" sizes="(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px" /></a><p class="wp-caption-text">Mayor Richard J. Daley speaks at an Old Parish event to commemorate him during his visit to Ireland. Eleanor &#8220;Sis&#8221; Daley is among those seated on the dais, 1964. RJD_04_01_0042_0001_034</p></div>
<p>Local officials unveiled this plaque:</p>
<blockquote><p>This plantation containing ten acres was financed by the contributions of some friends and associates of Richard J. Daley Mayor of Chicago, to whose honour it is dedicated. A.D. 1959</p></blockquote>
<div id="attachment_4807" style="width: 310px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><a href="https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2019/04/RJD_04_01_0023_0013_018.jpg"><img class="size-medium wp-image-4807" src="https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2019/04/RJD_04_01_0023_0013_018-300x225.jpg" alt="Unveiling of the Daley family homestead monument at Monameean during Daley's trip to Ireland, 1964" width="300" height="225" srcset="https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2019/04/RJD_04_01_0023_0013_018-300x225.jpg 300w, https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2019/04/RJD_04_01_0023_0013_018-768x577.jpg 768w, https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2019/04/RJD_04_01_0023_0013_018-510x382.jpg 510w, https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2019/04/RJD_04_01_0023_0013_018.jpg 964w" sizes="(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px" /></a><p class="wp-caption-text">Unveiling of the Daley family homestead monument at Monameean during Daley&#8217;s trip to Ireland, 1964. R. Wiley, photographer. RJD_04_01_0023_0013_018</p></div>
<h2>More photographs</h2>
<a href='http://collections.carli.illinois.edu/cdm/search/collection/uic_rjdaley/searchterm/1964!voyages%20and%20travels/field/all!subjea/mode/all!all/conn/and!and/order/title/ad/asc' class='small-button smalllightblue' target="_blank">See more images from Mayor Richard J. Daley&#8217;s 1964 trip to Europe</a>
<p>These photographs come from the Richard J. Daley Collection, housed in the <a href="https://library.uic.edu/special-collections-university-archives">Special Collections and University Archives of the University of Illinois at Chicago Library</a>. Most of the photographs in this collection have been digitized and are available online in the <a href="http://collections.carli.illinois.edu/cdm/landingpage/collection/uic_rjdaley">Richard J. Daley Era Photograph Collection</a>. For questions about the photographs or about making an appointment to <a href="https://library.uic.edu/help/article/2990/visit-special-collections-and-university-archives">visit UIC Special Collections</a>, feel free to <a href="https://library.uic.edu/contact">Ask a Librarian</a>.</p>
