			<article id="post-4724" class="et_pb_post clearfix et_pb_no_thumb post-4724 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-news-and-research-funds">

			
												<h2 class="entry-title"><a href="https://rjd.library.uic.edu/remembering-1989-chicago-mayor-richard-m-daleys-first-inauguration/">Remembering 1989: Chicago Mayor Richard M. Daley&#8217;s first inauguration</a></h2>
				
				<p class="post-meta">  <span class="published">Apr 24, 2019</span>    </p><div class="post-content"><p>Thirty years ago today, on April 24, 1989, Richard M. Daley was sworn in as Chicago&#8217;s mayor for the first of what would be six terms in office. This photograph comes from the Richard M. Daley papers, the processed portions of which are open to researchers. Please see the <a href="https://researchguides.uic.edu/daleyfamily">Daley Family research guide</a> for more information.</p>
<div id="attachment_4730" style="width: 2010px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><a href="https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2019/03/RMD_01_313_0007_001.jpg"><img class="size-full wp-image-4730" src="https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2019/03/RMD_01_313_0007_001.jpg" alt="Scene from Mayor Richard M. Daley's first inauguration, with a copy of the inaugural program" width="2000" height="1392" srcset="https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2019/03/RMD_01_313_0007_001.jpg 2000w, https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2019/03/RMD_01_313_0007_001-300x209.jpg 300w, https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2019/03/RMD_01_313_0007_001-768x535.jpg 768w, https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2019/03/RMD_01_313_0007_001-1024x713.jpg 1024w, https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2019/03/RMD_01_313_0007_001-1080x752.jpg 1080w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /></a><p class="wp-caption-text">Scene from Mayor Richard M. Daley&#8217;s first inauguration, with a copy of the inaugural program. RMD_01_313_0007_001</p></div>
</div>			
			</article> <!-- .et_pb_post -->
	
			<article id="post-4689" class="et_pb_post clearfix et_pb_no_thumb post-4689 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-news-and-research-funds">

			
												<h2 class="entry-title"><a href="https://rjd.library.uic.edu/sixty-years-since-richard-j-daleys-first-re-election-as-mayor/">Sixty years since Richard J. Daley&#8217;s first re-election as mayor</a></h2>
				
				<p class="post-meta">  <span class="published">Apr 7, 2019</span>    </p><div class="post-content"><p>Today marks Mayor Richard J. Daley&#8217;s first re-election as mayor on April 7, 1959.</p>
<div id="attachment_4693" style="width: 251px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><a href="https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2019/03/RJD_04_01_0015_0003_013.jpg"><img class="size-medium wp-image-4693" src="https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2019/03/RJD_04_01_0015_0003_013-241x300.jpg" alt="Chicago Mayor Richard J. Daley stands next to stack of petitions to place his name for re-election, 1959." width="241" height="300" srcset="https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2019/03/RJD_04_01_0015_0003_013-241x300.jpg 241w, https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2019/03/RJD_04_01_0015_0003_013-768x955.jpg 768w, https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2019/03/RJD_04_01_0015_0003_013.jpg 772w" sizes="(max-width: 241px) 100vw, 241px" /></a><p class="wp-caption-text">Chicago Mayor Richard J. Daley stands next to stack of petitions to place his name for re-election, 1959. RJD_04_01_0015_0003_013</p></div>
<div id="attachment_4696" style="width: 254px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><a href="https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2019/03/RJD_04_01_0015_0003_003.jpg"><img class="size-medium wp-image-4696" src="https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2019/03/RJD_04_01_0015_0003_003-244x300.jpg" alt="Chicago Mayor Richard J. Daley jokes with a supporter during a re-election campaign, 1959" width="244" height="300" srcset="https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2019/03/RJD_04_01_0015_0003_003-244x300.jpg 244w, https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2019/03/RJD_04_01_0015_0003_003-768x946.jpg 768w, https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2019/03/RJD_04_01_0015_0003_003.jpg 770w" sizes="(max-width: 244px) 100vw, 244px" /></a><p class="wp-caption-text">Chicago Mayor Richard J. Daley jokes with a supporter during a re-election campaign, 1959. RJD_04_01_0015_0003_003</p></div>
<p>Daley&#8217;s victory was huge. He garnered more than 777,000 votes while his Republican opponent, Tim Sheehan, polled only around 312,000.</p>
<div id="attachment_4701" style="width: 310px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><a href="https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2019/03/RJD_04_01_0015_0005_006.jpg"><img class="size-medium wp-image-4701" src="https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2019/03/RJD_04_01_0015_0005_006-300x244.jpg" alt="Mayor Richard J. Daley and Eleanor &quot;Sis&quot; Daley greet well-wishers at the mayor's inauguration for his second term, 1959" width="300" height="244" srcset="https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2019/03/RJD_04_01_0015_0005_006-300x244.jpg 300w, https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2019/03/RJD_04_01_0015_0005_006-768x624.jpg 768w, https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2019/03/RJD_04_01_0015_0005_006.jpg 952w" sizes="(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px" /></a><p class="wp-caption-text">Mayor Richard J. Daley and Eleanor &#8220;Sis&#8221; Daley greet well-wishers at the mayor&#8217;s inauguration for his second term, 1959. RJD_04_01_0015_0005_006</p></div>
<h2>Work consulted</h2>
<p>Tagge, George. &#8220;Daley Elected by 465,000,&#8221; <em>Chicago Tribune</em>, April 8, 1959, p. 1.</p>
</div>			
			</article> <!-- .et_pb_post -->
	
			<article id="post-4678" class="et_pb_post clearfix et_pb_no_thumb post-4678 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-news-and-research-funds">

			
												<h2 class="entry-title"><a href="https://rjd.library.uic.edu/remembering-1989-richard-m-daley-elected-mayor-of-chicago/">Remembering 1989: Richard M. Daley elected mayor of Chicago</a></h2>
				
				<p class="post-meta">  <span class="published">Apr 4, 2019</span>    </p><div class="post-content"><p>On this date in 1989, Richard M. Daley won election as Chicago&#8217;s 54th mayor. He went on to serve a total of six terms, stepping down in 2011.</p>
<div id="attachment_4681" style="width: 959px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><a href="https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2019/04/RMD_07_0057_0002_003.jpg"><img class="size-full wp-image-4681" src="https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2019/04/RMD_07_0057_0002_003.jpg" alt="Mayor Richard M. Daley." width="949" height="1200" srcset="https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2019/04/RMD_07_0057_0002_003.jpg 949w, https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2019/04/RMD_07_0057_0002_003-237x300.jpg 237w, https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2019/04/RMD_07_0057_0002_003-768x971.jpg 768w, https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2019/04/RMD_07_0057_0002_003-810x1024.jpg 810w" sizes="(max-width: 949px) 100vw, 949px" /></a><p class="wp-caption-text">Mayor Richard M. Daley. RMD_07_0057_0002_003.</p></div>
<p>This photograph comes from the Richard M. Daley Papers, the processed portions of which are open to the public. For more information on doing research in the Richard M. Daley Papers, the Richard J. Daley Collection, and related collections, please see our <a href="https://researchguides.uic.edu/DaleyFamily/Home">research guide for the Daley Family Collections</a>.</p>
</div>			
