			<article id="post-4596" class="et_pb_post clearfix et_pb_no_thumb post-4596 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-news-and-research-funds">

			
												<h2 class="entry-title"><a href="https://rjd.library.uic.edu/featuring-the-martin-h-kennelly-papers/">Featuring: the Martin H. Kennelly Papers</a></h2>
				
				<p class="post-meta">  <span class="published">Jan 18, 2019</span>    </p><div class="post-content"><p>UIC Special Collections and University Archives holds the <a href="https://findingaids.library.uic.edu/sc/MSKenn77.xml">papers of Martin H. Kennelly</a>, who served as Chicago&#8217;s mayor from 1947 to 1955. During his time in office, Kennelly gained a reputation for honesty and for running a businesslike administration.</p>
<div id="attachment_4606" style="width: 250px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><a href="https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2019/01/RJD_04_01_0009_0007_014.jpg"><img class="size-medium wp-image-4606" src="https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2019/01/RJD_04_01_0009_0007_014-240x300.jpg" alt="Portrait of Mayor Martin Kennelly" width="240" height="300" srcset="https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2019/01/RJD_04_01_0009_0007_014-240x300.jpg 240w, https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2019/01/RJD_04_01_0009_0007_014.jpg 761w" sizes="(max-width: 240px) 100vw, 240px" /></a><p class="wp-caption-text">Martin Kennelly, ca. 1950s. RJD_04_01_0009_0007_014</p></div>
<p>Kennelly maintained ties with his fellow Democrats nationally and locally.</p>
<div id="attachment_4611" style="width: 310px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><a href="https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2019/01/RJD_04_01_0001_0012_005.jpg"><img class="size-medium wp-image-4611" src="https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2019/01/RJD_04_01_0001_0012_005-300x236.jpg" alt="Mayor Martin Kennelly speaks at a Truman campaign event, ca. 1948" width="300" height="236" srcset="https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2019/01/RJD_04_01_0001_0012_005-300x236.jpg 300w, https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2019/01/RJD_04_01_0001_0012_005-768x604.jpg 768w, https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2019/01/RJD_04_01_0001_0012_005.jpg 965w" sizes="(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px" /></a><p class="wp-caption-text">Mayor Martin Kennelly speaks at a Truman campaign event, ca. 1948. RJD_04_01_0001_0012_005</p></div>
<div id="attachment_4615" style="width: 257px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><a href="https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2019/01/RJD_04_01_0002_0010_007.jpg"><img class="size-medium wp-image-4615" src="https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2019/01/RJD_04_01_0002_0010_007-247x300.jpg" alt="11th Ward Picnic, Richard J. Daley and Martin Kennelly, August 21, 1949" width="247" height="300" srcset="https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2019/01/RJD_04_01_0002_0010_007-247x300.jpg 247w, https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2019/01/RJD_04_01_0002_0010_007-768x935.jpg 768w, https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2019/01/RJD_04_01_0002_0010_007.jpg 784w" sizes="(max-width: 247px) 100vw, 247px" /></a><p class="wp-caption-text">11th Ward Picnic, Richard J. Daley and Martin Kennelly, August 21, 1949. RJD_04_01_0002_0010_007</p></div>
<div id="attachment_4618" style="width: 310px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><a href="https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2019/01/RJD_04_01_0010_0002_009.jpg"><img class="size-medium wp-image-4618" src="https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2019/01/RJD_04_01_0010_0002_009-300x239.jpg" alt="Mayor Martin Kennelly, Richard J. Daley, and John Mortimer display newspapers after the mayor's re-election" width="300" height="239" srcset="https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2019/01/RJD_04_01_0010_0002_009-300x239.jpg 300w, https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2019/01/RJD_04_01_0010_0002_009-768x613.jpg 768w, https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2019/01/RJD_04_01_0010_0002_009.jpg 952w" sizes="(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px" /></a><p class="wp-caption-text">Mayor Martin Kennelly, Richard J. Daley, and John Mortimer display newspapers after the mayor&#8217;s re-election, 1951. RJD_04_01_0010_0002_009</p></div>
<p>In 1955, Richard J. Daley, who was Cook County Clerk at the time, ran against Kennelly for the Democratic Party&#8217;s nomination for mayor. Kennelly lost, and Daley went on to win the mayor&#8217;s race that year.</p>
<p>In his inaugural address, Daley thanked the outgoing mayor:</p>
<blockquote><p>I want to express the appreciation and admiration which I know all the people of Chicago have for the administration of Martin Kennelly. He will always be remembered as a mayor who made important contributions to his city.</p></blockquote>
<p>The <a href="https://findingaids.library.uic.edu/sc/MSKenn77.xml">Martin H. Kennelly Papers</a> holds more than 130 linear feet of materials and consists primarily of speeches, correspondence, and newspaper clippings from Kennelly&#8217;s three mayoral campaigns and his eight years in office. The collection is open to the public and researchers may access them by <a href="https://library.uic.edu/help/article/2990/visit-special-collections-and-university-archives">visiting UIC Special Collections and University Archives in the Richard J. Daley Library</a>.</p>
<h3>Sources consulted</h3>
<p>Daley, Richard J. &#8220;Inaugural Address of Richard J. Daley, Mayor.&#8221; Richard J. Daley Collection, Special Collections and University Archives. Series 1, subseries 1, box 21, folder 4.</p>
<p>Martin H. Kennelly Papers, finding aid. &lt;<a href="https://findingaids.library.uic.edu/sc/MSKenn77.xml">https://findingaids.library.uic.edu/sc/MSKenn77.xm</a>l&gt;. Accessed January 17, 2019.</p>
<p>Richard J. Daley Era Photographs (University of Illinois at Chicago). CARLI digital collections. &lt;<a href="http://collections.carli.illinois.edu/cdm/landingpage/collection/uic_rjdaley">http://collections.carli.illinois.edu/cdm/landingpage/collection/uic_rjdaley</a>&gt;. Accessed January 17, 2019.</p>
</div>			
			</article> <!-- .et_pb_post -->
	
			<article id="post-4576" class="et_pb_post clearfix et_pb_no_thumb post-4576 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-news-and-research-funds">

			
												<h2 class="entry-title"><a href="https://rjd.library.uic.edu/no-place-like-home/">No place like home</a></h2>
				
				<p class="post-meta">  <span class="published">Jan 4, 2019</span>    </p><div class="post-content"><p>Eighty years ago, Richard J. Daley and Eleanor &#8220;Sis&#8221; Daley moved into their home in Bridgeport, the Chicago neighborhood where they had both grown up. The Daleys purchased two lots of land and had the house built quickly. &#8220;On August 15 we broke ground. We moved in on November 15,&#8221; <a href="https://blog.library.uic.edu/transcript_files/Daley,%20Eleanor%2020020718.pdf">Eleanor recalled in an oral history interview she gave on July 18, 2002 [PDF]</a>.</p>
<div id="attachment_4585" style="width: 310px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><a href="https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2019/01/MSLASZ13_0002_0003_002.jpg"><img class="size-medium wp-image-4585" src="https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2019/01/MSLASZ13_0002_0003_002-300x241.jpg" alt="Image of the Daley family home in Bridgeport" width="300" height="241" srcset="https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2019/01/MSLASZ13_0002_0003_002-300x241.jpg 300w, https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2019/01/MSLASZ13_0002_0003_002-768x618.jpg 768w, https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2019/01/MSLASZ13_0002_0003_002.jpg 963w" sizes="(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px" /></a><p class="wp-caption-text">The Daley family home in Bridgeport. Photo: LÃ¡szlÃ³ Kondor. MSLASZ13_0002_0003_002</p></div>
<div id="attachment_4591" style="width: 249px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><a href="https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2019/01/MSLASZ13_0004_0011_024.jpg"><img class="size-medium wp-image-4591" src="https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2019/01/MSLASZ13_0004_0011_024-239x300.jpg" alt="Mayor Richard J. and Eleanor &quot;Sis&quot; Daley outside their home on St. Patrick's Day, circa 1972-1976." width="239" height="300" srcset="https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2019/01/MSLASZ13_0004_0011_024-239x300.jpg 239w, https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2019/01/MSLASZ13_0004_0011_024-768x965.jpg 768w, https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2019/01/MSLASZ13_0004_0011_024.jpg 794w" sizes="(max-width: 239px) 100vw, 239px" /></a><p class="wp-caption-text">Mayor Richard J. and Eleanor &#8220;Sis&#8221; Daley outside their home on St. Patrick&#8217;s Day, circa 1972-1976. Photo LÃ¡szlÃ³ Kondor. MSLASZ13_0004_0011_024</p></div>
<h2>Source</h2>
<p><a href="https://blog.library.uic.edu/transcript_files/Daley,%20Eleanor%2020020718.pdf">Interview with Eleanor &#8220;Sis&#8221; Daley, July 18, 2002 [PDF]</a>. Richard J. Daley Oral History Collection, Special Collections and University Archives, University of Illinois at Chicago.</p>
</div>			
			</article> <!-- .et_pb_post -->
	
			<article id="post-4553" class="et_pb_post clearfix et_pb_no_thumb post-4553 post type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-news-and-research-funds">

			
												<h2 class="entry-title"><a href="https://rjd.library.uic.edu/the-snows-of-yesteryear-in-chicago/">The snows of yesteryear&#8230;in Chicago!</a></h2>
				
				<p class="post-meta">  <span class="published">Jan 1, 2019</span>    </p><div class="post-content"><div id="attachment_4559" style="width: 966px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><a href="https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2018/12/RJD_04_01_0043_0006_001.jpg"><img class="size-full wp-image-4559" src="https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2018/12/RJD_04_01_0043_0006_001.jpg" alt="Richard J. Daley and a group of boys shovel snow." width="956" height="729" srcset="https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2018/12/RJD_04_01_0043_0006_001.jpg 956w, https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2018/12/RJD_04_01_0043_0006_001-300x229.jpg 300w, https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2018/12/RJD_04_01_0043_0006_001-768x586.jpg 768w" sizes="(max-width: 956px) 100vw, 956px" /></a><p class="wp-caption-text">A group of boys, including a young Richard J. Daley, shovel snow. Circa 1910. Photographer: Friesleben. RJD_04_01_0043_0006_001</p></div>
</div>			
			</article> <!-- .et_pb_post -->
	
			<article id="post-4534" class="et_pb_post clearfix et_pb_no_thumb post-4534 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-news-and-research-funds">

			
												<h2 class="entry-title"><a href="https://rjd.library.uic.edu/featuring-the-edmund-kasper-jarecki-papers-at-uic/">Featuring: the Edmund Kasper Jarecki Papers at UIC</a></h2>
				
				<p class="post-meta">  <span class="published">Dec 6, 2018</span>    </p><div class="post-content"><p>Edmund Kasper Jarecki (1879-1966) served Chicago in a number of capacities. In 1908 he represented what was then the city&#8217;s 16th Ward. From 1914 to 1920, he served as judge of the municipal court. In 1922 he won election to the Cook County court, where he stayed for more than 30 years and earned a reputation as a champion for honesty in city elections.</p>
<div id="attachment_4543" style="width: 310px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><a href="https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2018/12/RJD_04_01_0008_0004_020.jpg"><img class="size-medium wp-image-4543" src="https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2018/12/RJD_04_01_0008_0004_020-300x254.jpg" alt="Cook County Clerk Richard J. Daley administers the oath of office to Judge Edmund Kasper Jarecki in 1954." width="300" height="254" srcset="https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2018/12/RJD_04_01_0008_0004_020-300x254.jpg 300w, https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2018/12/RJD_04_01_0008_0004_020-768x650.jpg 768w, https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2018/12/RJD_04_01_0008_0004_020.jpg 996w" sizes="(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px" /></a><p class="wp-caption-text">Cook County Clerk Richard J. Daley administers the oath of office to Judge Edmund Kasper Jarecki. RJD_04_01_0008_0004_020.</p></div>
<p>Upon Jarecki&#8217;s retirement in 1954, the Cook County Democratic Party noted his &#8220;outstanding ability, unimpeachable integrity and unquestioned honesty&#8221; in a resolution commending him for his years of service.</p>
<p>The University of Illinois at Chicago houses Judge Jarecki&#8217;s papers. The materials in this collection document the judge&#8217;s many years of service as well as aspects of his personal life. See the <a href="https://findingaids.library.uic.edu/sc/MSJare67.xml">finding aid (inventory list) for the Edmund Kasper Jarecki Papers</a> for more information.</p>
<p>Note: Quotation comes from the Richard J. Daley Collection, Special Collections and University Archives, University of Illinois at Chicago. Box SIss1B18, folder 1.</p>
</div>			
			</article> <!-- .et_pb_post -->
	
			<article id="post-4527" class="et_pb_post clearfix et_pb_no_thumb post-4527 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-news-and-research-funds">

			
												<h2 class="entry-title"><a href="https://rjd.library.uic.edu/thanksgiving/">Thanksgiving!</a></h2>
				
				<p class="post-meta">  <span class="published">Nov 21, 2018</span>    </p><div class="post-content"><p><a href="https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2018/11/RJD_04_01_0028_0012_002c.jpg"><img class="size-full wp-image-4528 aligncenter" src="https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2018/11/RJD_04_01_0028_0012_002c.jpg" alt="Card says &quot;Happy Thanksgiving&quot;" width="305" height="445" srcset="https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2018/11/RJD_04_01_0028_0012_002c.jpg 305w, https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2018/11/RJD_04_01_0028_0012_002c-206x300.jpg 206w" sizes="(max-width: 305px) 100vw, 305px" /></a><br />
A Thanksgiving Day card from friends to the Daley family. From the Richard J. Daley Collection, RJD_04_01_0028_0012_002c.</p>
</div>			
			</article> <!-- .et_pb_post -->
	
			<article id="post-4477" class="et_pb_post clearfix et_pb_no_thumb post-4477 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-news-and-research-funds">

			
												<h2 class="entry-title"><a href="https://rjd.library.uic.edu/before-he-was-mayor/">Before he was mayor</a></h2>
				
				<p class="post-meta">  <span class="published">Nov 8, 2018</span>    </p><div class="post-content"><p>Eighty years ago today, Richard J. Daley won election to the Illinois State Senate after serving one term in the state&#8217;s house of representatives. In the image below, Daley stands to the right with his fellow senators.</p>
<div id="attachment_783" style="width: 1034px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><a href="https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2015/04/RJD_04_01_0001_0003_003.jpg"><img class="size-large wp-image-783" src="https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2015/04/RJD_04_01_0001_0003_003-1024x821.jpg" alt="Richard J. Daley's first session in the Illinois Senate." width="1024" height="821" srcset="https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2015/04/RJD_04_01_0001_0003_003-1024x821.jpg 1024w, https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2015/04/RJD_04_01_0001_0003_003-300x241.jpg 300w, https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2015/04/RJD_04_01_0001_0003_003-1080x866.jpg 1080w, https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2015/04/RJD_04_01_0001_0003_003.jpg 1200w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /></a><p class="wp-caption-text">Richard J. Daley&#8217;s first session in the Illinois Senate. Daley is standing on the right. RJD_04_01_0001_0003_003</p></div>
<p>For more images from the Richard J. Daley Collection, see the <a href="http://collections.carli.illinois.edu/cdm/landingpage/collection/uic_rjdaley">Richard J. Daley Era Photographs</a>.</p>
</div>			
			</article> <!-- .et_pb_post -->
	
